50
00:02:36,742 --> 00:02:44,867
There's no universal "better" database—both PostgreSQL and MongoDB are excellent choices depending on your requirements.

51
00:02:44,867 --> 00:02:50,444
PostgreSQL shines for complex relationships, transactions, and analytics.

52
00:02:50,444 --> 00:02:56,478
MongoDB excels with flexible schemas, horizontal scaling, and document-centric data.

53
00:02:56,478 --> 00:03:02,067
Consider your data model, query patterns, scaling needs, and team expertise when choosing.

